medical_history.chief_complaint: Acute onset of epigastric pain with nausea and vomiting.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: Symptoms began acutely 2 hours prior to presentation. The pain is constant, intense, and radiates to the back. There have been no recent medication changes or foreign travel, and the patient has never experienced this pain before. Pain is difficult to breathe through.
medical_history.past_medical_history: Colonic adenoma, impaired glucose tolerance, sleep disorder/disturbance (unspecified), urinary incontinence (unspecified), pulmonary nodule/lesion (solitary), thyroid nodule, monoclonal (M) protein disease (multiple myeloma), history of stem cell transplant, neuropathy due to drugs, dyspnea, positive PPD, cough, chronic chest and rib pain (into anterior neck).
medical_history.family_history: Her father died in an accident. Her mother does not have any medical problems.
